body: Hopefully that PR will fix it. May take a couple of days to get a nuget package onto the nuget test repo for validation.

Is it possible to try building with ORT v1.10 to see if that works? Would give another data point as _OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_ROCM should have been excluded from an iOS build in that release.
@enny1170 please can you share a binlog with us?

> Is it possible to try building with ORT v1.10 to see if that works? Would give another data point as _OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_ROCM should have been excluded from an iOS build in that release.

Building with ORT v1.10 works without errors. It is possible to build with v1.11 when setting the linker behavior to: "enable framework SDKs only".
As a workaround: I currently set ORT to v1.10 when debugging with linking disabled and update ORT to v1.11 for the release with linking enabled. Otherwise, each build takes over 3 minutes and hot reload doesn't work with linking.

Awesome. Thanks for the info and valuable tips around usage @smilingjack10. Much appreciated. Issue should be fixed in the next ORT release. 

If you want to test things out prior to that, you could possibly download the two nuget packages from https://aiinfra.visualstudio.com/PublicPackages/_artifacts/feed/ORT-Nightly. Those are published from the current builds with the latest code. Download to a folder and setup that folder as a nuget source.

Hi together, 
FYI: we had the same issue and the preview nuget from @skottmckay fixed it. 

Thank you. 

BTW: It is not specific to Apple M1
Should be resolved with the 1.12 release.
